          { "feature": "elevated_jvp_hepatojugular_reflux_positive", "weight": 5 },
          { "feature": "pulmonary_edema_on_chest_xray", "weight": 5 },
          { "feature": "elevated_bnp_or_nt_pro_bnp", "weight": 5 }
        ],
        "management": "Intravenous loop diuretic (furosemide IV 2x oral dose, or bumetanide/torsemide). Monitor I/O, daily weight, electrolytes. If refractory, add thiazide diuretic for sequential nephron blockade. Vasodilators (nitroglycerin IV or nitroprusside) if SBP >110. Inotropes (dobutamine or milrinone) if cardiogenic shock. Treat precipitating cause (ischemia, arrhythmia, infection)."
